OL,3,CFarm fined for multiple health and
OL,4,Csafety breaches after bull escape
OL,6,F"In the case at Seymour Stevens farm,
OL,7,Fthere were failings to manage health
OL,8,Fand safety risks associated with
OL,9,Fanimals and falling objects - two of
OL,10,Fthe five most common causes of fatal
OL,11,Finjuries in the agriculture sector."
OL,13,FSeymour Stevens Limited pleaded guilty
OL,14,Fto breaching section 2(1) of the
OL,15,FHealth and Safety at Work etc. act
OL,16,F1974 and was fined #12,000 and ordered
OL,17,Fto pay #4,830 in costs at a hearing at
OL,18,FMaidstone Magistrates' Court last week.
